    "media:imagetext": "TWA - TRANS WORLD AIRLINES\nLOCKHEED L749\nEntering service with TWA as \"Star of Madrid\"\nin 1948,\nN91202 was later named \"Star of Pennsylvania\"\nshown at\nKansas City in the Starstream paint scheme worn by a few\n\"Connies\" in the mid-60's, shortly before being withdrawn\nfrom use. N91202 was scrapped at Kansas City in 1968.\nAviation Views, 4333 Virginia, K.C., Mo. 64110\nPOST\nCARD\nRATE\n951189\nLitho in U.S.A.\nLO-01 584\nPOST CARD\nPhoto by Winston Golitz\nN91202, C/N-2578\n2001.082.003",
